  <title>Glossary</title>
  
  <para>
    This part contains descriptions of the phrases used when writing
    and talking about dCache.  Depending on the context this might
    just be a glossary which is referenced by the remainder of this
    guide. It contains also information about the PNFS server, since
    its concepts heavily influence dCache.
  </para>

  <chapter id="gl-general">
    <title>General</title>

    <glosslist>

      <glossentry>
	<glossterm id="gl-tape_backend">tape backend</glossterm>
	<glossdef>
	  <para>
	    A mass storage system which stores data on magnetic tapes
	    and is connected to the dCache system. Each dCache pool
	    will write files to a tape backend as soon as they have
	    been completely written to the pool (if the pool is not
	    configured as a <glossterm
	    linkend="gl-lfs">LFS</glossterm>). The tape system is not
	    part of dCache. However, it is possible to use any mass
	    storage system as tape backend via a simple interface.
	  </para>
	</glossdef>
      </glossentry>


      <glossentry>
	<glossterm id="gl-hsm">Hierachical Storage Manager (<abbrev>HSM</abbrev>)</glossterm>
	<abbrev>HSM</abbrev>
	<glosssee otherterm="gl-tape_backend">tape backend</glosssee>
      </glossentry>
      
      <glossentry>
	<glossterm id="gl-lfs">Large File Store (<abbrev>LFS</abbrev>)</glossterm>
	<abbrev>LFS</abbrev>
	<glossdef>
	  <para>
	    If a dCache instance does not have a <glossterm
	    linkend="gl-tape_backend">tape backend</glossterm>, it is
	    not a cache but a large file store. There are two lfs
	    modes: <glossterm>precious</glossterm> and
	    <glossterm>transient</glossterm> mode.
	  </para>
	</glossdef>
      </glossentry>
      
      <glossentry>
	<glossterm id="gl-store">to store</glossterm>
	<glossdef>
	  <para>
	    Copying a file from a dCache pool to the <glossterm
	    linkend="gl-tape_backend">tape backend</glossterm>.
	  </para>
	</glossdef>
      </glossentry>
      
      <glossentry>
	<glossterm id="gl-restore">to restore</glossterm>
	<glossdef>
	  <para>
	    Copying a file from the <glossterm
	    linkend="gl-tape_backend">tape backend</glossterm> to one
	    of the dCache pools.
	  </para>
	</glossdef>
      </glossentry>
      
      <glossentry>
	<glossterm id="gl-stage">to stage</glossterm>
	<glosssee otherterm="gl-restore">to restore</glosssee>
      </glossentry>

      <glossentry>
	<glossterm id="gl-transfer">transfer</glossterm>
	<glossdef>
	  <para>
	    Any kind of transfer performed by a dCache pool. There are
	    <glossterm linkend="gl-store">store</glossterm>,
	    <glossterm linkend="gl-restore">restore</glossterm>, read
	    and write transfers. The latter two are client transfers.
	  </para>
	  <glossseealso otherterm="gl-mover">mover</glossseealso>
	</glossdef>
      </glossentry>

      <glossentry>
	<glossterm id="gl-mover">mover</glossterm>
	<glossdef>
	  <para>
	    The process/tread within a pool which performs a
	    <glossterm linkend="gl-transfer">transfer</glossterm>.
	  </para>
	  <glossseealso otherterm="gl-transfer">transfer</glossseealso>
	</glossdef>
      </glossentry>

    </glosslist>

  </chapter>

